---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LegalContent from '../../components/legal/LegalContent.astro';
import { useTranslations } from '../../i18n/utils';

const locale = 'en' as const;
const t = useTranslations(locale);
---
<BaseLayout title={t('legal.datenschutzTitle')} locale={locale}>
  <main>
    <LegalContent title="Privacy policy">
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> April 2026</p>
      <p>
        <em>This translation is provided for convenience. The German version on
        /datenschutz is the legally binding text.</em>
      </p>

      <h2>§ 1 Controller</h2>
      <p>Controller within the meaning of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):</p>
      <address>
        Nestor Segura<br />
        Heidmühlenweg 54<br />
        25336 Elmshorn<br />
        Germany<br /><br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:contact@nestorsegura.com">contact@nestorsegura.com</a>
      </address>

      <h2>§ 2 General information on data processing</h2>
      <p>
        I take the protection of your personal data seriously. Personal data is treated
        confidentially and in accordance with the applicable data protection laws and this
        privacy policy.
      </p>
      <p>
        Data is collected only to the extent technically necessary. The data collected is
        not sold and — except as described in this policy — is not shared with third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 3 Hosting and technical provision</h2>
      <p>
        This website is hosted by Cloudflare (Cloudflare, Inc., 101 Townsend St, San Francisco,
        CA 94107, USA, and Cloudflare Germany GmbH, Rosental 7, c/o Mindspace, 80331 Munich).
        Content is delivered via the global Cloudflare network, with European edge locations
        preferred where possible.
      </p>
      <p>
        When you visit this site, technically necessary data is automatically processed in
        server log files:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>IP address of the requesting device (typically anonymised)</li>
        <li>Date and time of the request</li>
        <li>Name and URL of the file requested</li>
        <li>Referrer URL</li>
        <li>Browser used and, where applicable, the operating system</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Legal basis is Art. 6 (1) (f) GDPR (legitimate interest in error-free delivery and
        security of the website). Cloudflare is certified under the EU-US Data Privacy Framework.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 4 SSL/TLS encryption</h2>
      <p>
        This website uses SSL/TLS encryption to protect confidential content. You can recognise
        an encrypted connection by the “https://" prefix in the address bar and the lock icon
        in your browser bar.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 5 Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
      <h3>Strictly necessary cookies</h3>
      <p>
        Strictly necessary cookies and similar technologies (e.g. local storage to remember your
        cookie consent) are used to ensure proper operation of the website. Legal basis is
        Art. 6 (1) (f) GDPR and § 25 (2) no. 2 of the German TDDDG.
      </p>

      <h3>Analytics and marketing cookies</h3>
      <p>
        Cookies and tracking technologies for analytics and marketing (see §§ 6 and 7) are only
        set after your explicit consent via the cookie banner. Legal basis is Art. 6 (1) (a) GDPR
        and § 25 (1) TDDDG. You can withdraw your consent at any time via the “Cookie settings"
        button in the footer.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 6 Google Analytics 4</h2>
      <p>
        With your consent, this website uses Google Analytics 4, provided by Google Ireland
        Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland (“Google"). Google Analytics
        uses cookies and similar technologies to evaluate the use of the website. The information
        generated is generally transmitted to a Google server in the USA and stored there.
      </p>
      <h3>IP anonymisation</h3>
      <p>
        Google Analytics is used with the “IP anonymisation" feature enabled. Your IP address
        is shortened within the EU or the EEA before being transmitted to the USA.
      </p>
      <h3>Legal basis</h3>
      <p>
        Use is based on your consent in accordance with Art. 6 (1) (a) GDPR and § 25 (1) TDDDG.
        You can withdraw your consent at any time via the cookie banner. Google is certified under
        the EU-US Data Privacy Framework.
      </p>
      <h3>Opt-out</h3>
      <p>
        You can additionally prevent collection by Google Analytics by installing the browser
        add-on for deactivating Google Analytics:
        <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 7 Meta Pixel (Facebook Pixel)</h2>
      <p>
        With your consent, this website uses the Meta Pixel (also “Facebook Pixel") provided by
        Meta Platforms Ireland Limited, Merrion Road, Dublin 4, D04 X2K5, Ireland. The pixel allows
        the behaviour of users to be tracked after they have viewed or clicked on a Facebook or
        Instagram advertisement. This enables conversion tracking of Meta ads and the building of
        target groups for future ads (Custom Audiences).
      </p>
      <p>
        In doing so, personal data (in particular IP address, browser information and actions on
        the website) is transferred to Meta in the USA. Meta is certified under the EU-US Data
        Privacy Framework.
      </p>
      <p>
        Legal basis is your consent in accordance with Art. 6 (1) (a) GDPR and § 25 (1) TDDDG.
        You can withdraw your consent at any time via the cookie banner. Further information is
        available in Meta's privacy policy:
        <a href="https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy/</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 8 Appointment booking via TidyCal</h2>
      <p>
        For online appointment booking I use the TidyCal service (TidyCal, operated by SureSwift
        Capital, 800 Nicollet Mall, Suite 2675, Minneapolis, MN 55402, USA). When you book a
        slot via the TidyCal button, you are redirected to a TidyCal page or a TidyCal widget is
        embedded.
      </p>
      <p>Data processed typically includes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>First and last name</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Phone number, where applicable</li>
        <li>Any additional information you voluntarily provide</li>
        <li>The time slot you select</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Legal bases are Art. 6 (1) (b) GDPR (pre-contractual measures) and Art. 6 (1) (f) GDPR
        (legitimate interest in efficient scheduling).
      </p>

      <h2>§ 9 Content management via Sanity</h2>
      <p>
        The content of this website is maintained in the headless CMS Sanity (Sanity.io,
        c/o Sanity Inc., 301 Howard Street, Suite 600, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA) and is
        compiled into static HTML files at build time. When the site is requested, no connection
        to Sanity is normally made; Sanity processes only the data I edit as the operator in the
        backend.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 10 Fonts</h2>
      <p>
        This website uses self-hosted fonts only (“Clash Display" and “Chivo"). No connection
        to external font servers (e.g. Google Fonts) is established. Your IP address is not
        transmitted to any third-party font provider.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 11 Contact via email</h2>
      <p>
        If you contact me by email, the data you provide (your email address, possibly your
        name and phone number, and your message) is stored for the purpose of processing your
        enquiry and for any follow-up questions.
      </p>
      <p>
        Legal bases are Art. 6 (1) (b) GDPR (pre-contractual measures) and Art. 6 (1) (f) GDPR
        (legitimate interest in handling your enquiry). The data is deleted as soon as it is no
        longer required for the purpose for which it was collected and no statutory retention
        obligations exist.
      </p>

      <h2>§ 12 Your rights as a data subject</h2>
      <p>You have the following rights with regard to your personal data:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Right of access</strong> (Art. 15 GDPR)</li>
        <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> (Art. 16 GDPR)</li>
        <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> (Art. 17 GDPR)</li>
        <li><strong>Right to restriction of processing</strong> (Art. 18 GDPR)</li>
        <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> (Art. 20 GDPR)</li>
        <li><strong>Right to object</strong> (Art. 21 GDPR)</li>
        <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent</strong> (Art. 7 (3) GDPR), with effect for the future</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise your rights, please contact me using the details given in § 1.</p>

      <h2>§ 13 Right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</h2>
      <p>
        Without prejudice to any other administrative or judicial remedy, you have the right to
        lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority if you believe that the processing of
        your personal data infringes the GDPR. The supervisory authority responsible for me is:
      </p>
      <address>
        Independent State Centre for Data Protection Schleswig-Holstein (ULD)<br />
        Holstenstraße 98<br />
        24103 Kiel, Germany<br />
        <a href="https://www.datenschutzzentrum.de" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.datenschutzzentrum.de</a>
      </address>

      <h2>§ 14 Changes to this privacy policy</h2>
      <p>
        I reserve the right to amend this privacy policy so that it always meets current legal
        requirements or reflects changes in my services. The version currently published on this
        website applies.
      </p>
    </LegalContent>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
